WHAT IS DYNAMIC PROGRAMMING?

Definition: "Solve complex problem by breaking into overlapping subproblems, store results to avoid recomputation"

Key Insight: Use memoization (caching) to turn exponential to polynomial

SIMPLE EXAMPLE - Fibonacci:

Recursive (Inefficient - O(2^n)): fib(5) calls fib(4) + fib(3) fib(4) calls fib(3) + fib(2) fib(3) is computed TWICE!

DP (Efficient - O(n)): Instead of recomputing fib(3), store it in cache Next time fib(3) needed, look up in O(1) instead of recomputing

STEPS TO SOLVE DP PROBLEM:

Identify overlapping subproblems
Define subproblem: dp[i] = what?
Find recurrence: dp[i] = function of dp[i-1], dp[i-2], etc.
Base case: dp[0] = ?, dp[1] = ?
Build solution bottom-up